# Python Pipeline Standards
- Use modular, version-control-friendly scripts (.py) over notebooks.
- Use `torch.device('mps')` for Mac M3 acceleration in PyTorch/SAM tasks.
- Keep data processing logged to CSVs; use `pandas` for data handling.
- Aim for clean, readable code with type hints where possible.
- Never hardcode paths; use relative paths from the project root.